HEADWORD: Dispersonate
<hw>Dis*per"son'*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To deprive
of personality or individuality.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We multiply; we <qex>dispersonate</qex> ourselves.</q>
<rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dispirit</ent>⟦br⟧
